XSVD4I-yZhQ.title: HOW TO JOURNAL | JESSICA OLIE
XSVD4I-yZhQ.description:
This video is about journaling, why it’s useful, how to start journaling and when to journal. I’ve found it really therapeutic and empowering to write down my thoughts.
You don’t have to write a lot and everyday will be different. Some days you’ll have more to say than others and that’s completely normal.
1. Gratitude entry: write things you’re grateful for. No matter how big or small.
2. Write down your goals, your dreams, your aspirations. Use your journal to help manifest things that you want in your life. It’s such a powerful way to use your thoughts to bring about meaningful changes in your life and your thought patterns.
3. Write about your day.
4. Talk about your relationships, what’s happening in them.
5. Discuss your insecurities and how you want to overcome them.
6. Write about your fears and worries.

The most important thing is just putting your pen to paper and allowing your thoughts to flow freely without judgement.
This is your safe space!! 

J x


https://www.jessicaolie.com
